Operatives of Police Special Strike Force on Social Miscreants attached to Lagos State police command, yesterday said they have arrested a deadly Aiye Confraternity Kingpin Sikiru Samue(a.k.a ) Samora and eight members of his gang in Ikorodu area of the state and recovered one double barrel gun from the social miscreants. The Lagos State police public relations officer, Bala Elkana, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) who revealed this to journalists said the Lagos State Commissioner of Police, CP Hakeem Odumosu, deployed a Special Strike Force on Social Miscreants to Ikorodu, to sustain the ongoing onslaught on cultists and other social miscreants in Ikorodu, Imota, Agbowa, Owutu, Ijede, Ipakodo and Owode Onirin areas of the state. He said the operation, which is intelligence driven, recorded another remarkable achievement with the arrest of a deadly leader of Aiye confraternity, Sikiru Samuel a.k.a Samora 24 years old, at Imota while other members of his gang arrested were Adegboyega Ismaila, 19; Sunkanmi Shonubi, a.k.a Nape,l 19; Adigun Faruq, 18;  Rilwan Akinwale, 30; Victor Uju, a.k.a Zino, 18 ; Juwon Idowu  a.k.a lighter, 18 ; Rasak Adebola  a.k.a ‘Bobo, 20  and Kehinde Keshinro, 18. “The gang is responsible for series of violent attacks and gang violence in Imota and environs.” According to him, “One of such violent attacks happened on February 12,2020 at about 0830hours which led to the death of one David  Nwanga, 30 years old of Araro Adamo area. “The suspects were handed over to the homicide section of the State Criminal Investigation Department (CID), Yaba for discreet investigation and they will be charged to Court as soon as the investigation is over.’’